## 2. Third-Party Component: tetgen 1.5.1 (AGPL v3 License)
The `tetgen1.5.1` folder in this toolchain contains the complete source code of tetgen 1.5.1 and the compiled `tetgen.exe`. This component is copyrighted by its original author Hang Si and licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License (AGPL) v3.

### Compliance Statement for tetgen
1. Original Author: Hang Si
2. Official Website: https://wias-berlin.de/software/tetgen/
3. License Text: The full text of the AGPL v3 License is available in `tetgen1.5.1/AGPL-3.0.txt`
4. Source Code Access: The `tetgen1.5.1` folder contains the complete original source code of tetgen 1.5.1, which can be directly compiled to generate `tetgen.exe`
5. Derivative Constraints: If you modify the source code in the `tetgen1.5.1` folder and recompile it, you must open-source the modified source code in compliance with the AGPL v3 License.

## 3. Overall Compliance Requirements
1. When distributing this toolchain, you must retain this LICENSE file and shall not delete or alter the MIT License notice for self-developed code or the AGPL v3 License notice for tetgen;
2. When only using/distributing the tetgen binary file (`tetgen.exe`), ensure that the source code in the `tetgen1.5.1` folder is distributed together with the binary file;
3. Before commercial use, independently evaluate the constraints of the AGPL v3 License on commercial scenarios (e.g., open-sourcing relevant code is required for network service scenarios).